  "narrative": "surface_inventory_absence emits one data point per inline surface-scope declaration in verifier and gap-collector sources. At source_state sha256:4dd604720f0b2fc5eae51b324d6a6d798e57febb15de7a161cdfd4c80f63ea32 the collector found 24 occurrences across 14 files (distribution: 22 inline_scope_constant, 2 inline_walk_function). Each occurrence is one place where a file's 'what artifacts do I cover' knowledge is hardcoded inline rather than read from a unified surface inventory. surface_inventory (this proposal's candidate) emits one surface_inventory_entry data point per repo artifact (proposal/skill/foundation/meeting_note); once graduated, consuming files refactor to read from those data points and these gap occurrences become dangling. Closure: every gap_pointer above re-resolves dangling at a future source_state where the cited symbol no longer satisfies the absence_kind."
